body:
After I upgraded to React v0.12

When I require react with addons like so

```
var React = require('react/addons');
```

And make a simple component using an img node

```
var UsesImage = React.createClass({
  render: function () {
    return (<img src='http://placehold.it/350x150'/>);
  }
});
```

I get an error with the following trace:

```
ReactMount.findComponentRoot --> ReactMount.js:607
ReactMount.findReactNodeByID --> ReactMount.js:553
getNode --> ReactMount.js:129
ReactBrowserComponentMixin.getDOMNode --> ReactBrowserComponentMixin.js:36
LocalEventTrapMixin.trapBubbledEvent --> LocalEventTrapMixin.js:31
ReactCompositeComponent.createClass.componentDidMount --> ReactDOMImg.js:41
assign.notifyAll --> CallbackQueue.js:69
ON_DOM_READY_QUEUEING.close --> ReactReconcileTransaction.js:81
Mixin.closeAll --> Transaction.js:208
Mixin.perform --> Transaction.js:149
ReactComponent.Mixin.mountComponentIntoNode --> ReactComponent.js:382
(anonymous function)  --> ReactMount.js:313
wrapper --> ReactPerf.js:51
ReactMount.render --> ReactMount.js:382
wrapper --> ReactPerf.js:51
```

If I require react without addons, the error is resolved.

It also doesnt break on other node types.
For example, this worked for me:

```
var React = require('react/addons');

var UsesOther = React.createClass({
  render: function () {
    return (<h1>hello</h1>);
  }
});
```
